{
  "texts": [
    "Figure 14 illustrates, The ROC curve further strengthens the PolynetDWTCADx framework in classifying colorectal cancer across 24 classifications.",
    "The micro-average ROC curve was able to maintain consistent performance across all categories, as evidenced by an AUC of 0.95 and a macro-average ROC curve of 0.91.",
    "Class 16, which obtained a perfect AUC of 1.0, and Classes 4, 14, and 23, which achieved AUCs above 0.96, are notable highlights.",
    "These findings underscore the model's exceptional discriminatory capabilities, particularly with regard to clinically significant classes.",
    "Moreover, the ROC curves for other key classes, such as Class 6 (AUC: 0.94) and Class 13 (AUC: 0.98), demonstrate the framework's ability to effectively distinguish even subtle variations within the data."
  ]
}